# Testing Conventions

## Three Test Tiers

| Tier | Suffix | Location | Runner |
|------|--------|----------|--------|
| Unit / Component | `.test.ts` / `.test.tsx` | Co-located with source | Vitest |
| Integration | `.spec.ts` | `tests/integration/` | Playwright (via Vitest) |
| E2E | `.e2e.ts` | `tests/e2e/` | Playwright |

## Unit Tests (Vitest)
- Pure `.ts` tests run in Node environment
- `.tsx` component tests run in real Chromium (browser mode via `vitest-browser-react`)
- Title format: **sentence case**, "verb + object + context"

```typescript
describe('CounterForm', () => {
  it('increments the counter by 1 when submitted', async () => {});
  it('shows validation error when value is out of range', async () => {});
});
```

## Integration Tests
- Call API routes via `page.request.put(url, { data: {...} })`
- Pass `x-e2e-random-id` header for DB row isolation:

```typescript
const randomId = faker.string.uuid();
await page.request.put('/en/api/counter', {
  data: { increment: 1 },
  headers: { 'x-e2e-random-id': randomId },
});
```

## E2E Tests (Playwright)
- Always use `faker` to generate unique IDs: `const randomId = faker.string.uuid()`
- Set `x-e2e-random-id` cookie or header to isolate DB rows across parallel runs
- Use `page.goto()` → interact → assert pattern
- Visual tests capture screenshots for regression detection

## Storybook
- Stories co-located with component: `ComponentName.stories.tsx`
- Run via `@storybook/addon-vitest`
